12:31.758 --> 12:34.241
I'm collecting donations
for the Scarlet Cross

12:34.344 --> 12:35.689
on behalf of the victims.

12:35.793 --> 12:38.241
On days like today,

12:38.344 --> 12:41.689
posting on social media
isn't enough.

12:41.793 --> 12:46.379
What we need
is cold hard cash.

12:46.482 --> 12:48.862
I just got back
from the ATM,

12:48.965 --> 12:51.241
where I withdrew
the maximum amount

12:51.344 --> 12:53.344
of $300

12:53.448 --> 12:55.206
plus a $3.50 service fee.

12:55.310 --> 12:57.448
So...

12:57.551 --> 12:59.206
yeah.

12:59.310 --> 13:04.413
♪♪

13:04.517 --> 13:09.655
♪♪

13:09.758 --> 13:11.206
[ Distorted ]
Good job.

13:11.310 --> 13:17.586
♪♪

13:17.689 --> 13:24.310
♪♪

13:28.206 --> 13:29.551
Man: 80 dead.

13:29.655 --> 13:32.551
Hey, Paige,
I don't know if you heard,

13:32.655 --> 13:35.379
but I'm collecting donations
for the victims.

13:35.482 --> 13:36.586
Care to chip in?

13:36.689 --> 13:37.827
No.

13:37.931 --> 13:39.482
Wow.

13:39.586 --> 13:41.413
That's interesting
because I kind of

13:41.517 --> 13:42.931
thought you cared,
Paige,

13:43.034 --> 13:47.000
but now you don't want to donate
to the Scarlet Cross?

13:47.103 --> 13:49.758
I guess you haven't checked
the Internet today.

13:49.862 --> 13:51.896
Hey.Man: 81!

13:52.000 --> 13:54.517
BNN has been breaking
all of these stories

13:54.620 --> 13:57.137
about how problematic
the Scarlet Cross is

13:57.241 --> 13:59.137
and how they're cutting out
the hearts

13:59.241 --> 14:02.689
of poor Jamaican people
or something.

14:02.793 --> 14:04.206
Pretty sure
that's not true.

14:04.310 --> 14:06.206
Well, I posted it,
so it's true now.

14:06.310 --> 14:07.241
82!
Hey.

14:07.344 --> 14:08.586
Oh, and it looks like
a lot of people

14:08.689 --> 14:09.758
have liked my post.

14:09.862 --> 14:11.137
Hey. Hold on.
Hold on a second.

14:11.241 --> 14:13.034
You can't just have
your money back, okay?

14:13.137 --> 14:14.862
This belongs
to the victims now.

14:14.965 --> 14:17.206
It's kind of ironic
that you're collecting donations

14:17.310 --> 14:18.551
in a trash can because

14:18.655 --> 14:20.206
giving your money
to the Scarlet Cross

14:20.310 --> 14:22.655
is just like throwing it
in the trash.

14:22.758 --> 14:23.896
84!

14:24.000 --> 14:25.896
Well, now hold on.
Oh, my God.

14:26.000 --> 14:27.344
Look at yourselves,

14:27.448 --> 14:28.931
down there fighting
for money on the ground

14:29.034 --> 14:30.310
while people out there...

14:30.413 --> 14:32.965
Okay, now, wait a second!
$300 of that is mine.

14:33.068 --> 14:35.793
Man: 85!

14:35.896 --> 14:37.344
Kate, do we have
all the NDAs?

14:37.448 --> 14:39.241
We have a couple of stragglers,
but I'm working on it.

14:39.344 --> 14:40.379
Well, get them.

14:40.482 --> 14:41.586
One whistle-blower,

14:41.689 --> 14:43.034
and the FCC will
have their hands

14:43.137 --> 14:46.689
so far up our asses,
we'll have fingers for tongues.

14:46.793 --> 14:48.344
Did you get Richter?

14:48.448 --> 14:50.586
Let me talk to him.

14:50.689 --> 14:52.275
Hey.
How's it going?

14:52.379 --> 14:54.241
Andy Richter: Hiya, Chris.
Listen, I got a question.

14:54.344 --> 14:56.482
Would it be okay
if I did some improv?

14:56.586 --> 14:59.689
You know, I'm sort of one of
the better members of my team.

14:59.793 --> 15:02.172
Okay. Well...
you're the talent here, Andy.

15:02.275 --> 15:03.862
I have total faith
in you.

15:03.965 --> 15:06.620
Awesome.
Thanks, Chris. Bye.

15:06.724 --> 15:08.344
Jesus Christ.
Richter is going to blow it.

15:08.448 --> 15:10.206
I knew we should have pushed
harder for Tatum!

15:10.310 --> 15:13.655
Hey, Christian, relax.
This is the news.

15:13.758 --> 15:15.862
We do it every day,

15:15.965 --> 15:18.586
but there is one important thing
that you forgot.

15:18.689 --> 15:20.275
What?

15:20.379 --> 15:21.965
Have fun.

15:23.379 --> 15:25.344
♪♪

15:25.448 --> 15:27.448
Man: 91 dead.

15:27.551 --> 15:28.862
♪♪

15:28.965 --> 15:30.620
Happy birthday,
Grace.

15:30.724 --> 15:31.896
Nobody's doing
any work today,

15:32.000 --> 15:33.275
so I went out and got the cake
you wanted

15:33.379 --> 15:36.068
because I'm secretly
a great friend.

15:36.482 --> 15:38.965
Oh, yeah.

15:39.068 --> 15:41.241
That baker was pretty fucked up
by the tragedy.

15:41.344 --> 15:45.241
That's really sweet,
but no thanks.

15:45.344 --> 15:47.551
All I wanted for my birthday
was a slice of cake,

15:47.655 --> 15:51.103
but now everyone thinks
I'm a horrible, selfish person.

15:51.206 --> 15:52.137
Oh, please.

15:52.241 --> 15:54.758
Everyone is a horrible,
selfish person.

15:54.862 --> 15:56.379
It's just that today,
people feel helpless,

15:56.482 --> 15:58.862
and they're trying
to make themselves feel better,

15:58.965 --> 16:00.344
even though everything
they're doing is

16:00.448 --> 16:01.655
misguided and futile

16:01.758 --> 16:02.931
and might even hurt
other people,

16:03.034 --> 16:04.896
like voting
in a presidential election.

16:05.000 --> 16:07.344
Hey, guys. I just had
another selfless idea.

16:07.448 --> 16:09.517
I'm going to organize
a blood drive.

16:09.620 --> 16:11.551
Like Paige's
blood drive?

16:11.655 --> 16:13.034
How?!

16:13.137 --> 16:14.931
Matt, you're genuinely
a bad person.

16:15.034 --> 16:17.172
No, I'm not!
I'm good!

16:17.275 --> 16:19.689
Out of the way.
Universal donor coming through.

16:19.793 --> 16:22.034
Excuse me!

16:22.137 --> 16:23.793
Did you donate yet?

16:23.896 --> 16:26.689
Oh, I can't.
I have an iron deficiency.

16:26.793 --> 16:27.896
Of course you aren't
donating blood.

16:28.000 --> 16:29.655
You're just curating
everyone else's.

16:29.758 --> 16:31.137
How convenient.

16:31.241 --> 16:33.379
Guess I'll have to donate enough
for the both of us.

16:33.482 --> 16:36.827
Hi! I'd like to donate
a shit-ton of blood.

16:36.931 --> 16:39.482
♪♪

16:39.586 --> 16:43.172
Well, aren't you a big boy
with a big heart.

16:43.275 --> 16:44.172
Damn right.

16:44.275 --> 16:48.482
[ Monitor beeping rhythmically ]

16:48.586 --> 16:51.034
[ Echoing ] Wow.

16:51.137 --> 16:54.137
Add this to your pile, huh?

16:54.241 --> 16:58.137
It's so crazy how we all have
different types of blood.

16:58.241 --> 16:59.724
[ Chuckles ]
You're funny.

16:59.827 --> 17:01.172
Yeah.

17:01.275 --> 17:03.827
I'm kind of known
of the office class clown.

17:03.931 --> 17:05.793
Yeah, I bet you are.

17:05.896 --> 17:07.620
You're handsome, too.

17:07.724 --> 17:09.758
I got a haircut
last month.

17:09.862 --> 17:11.620
Wow.

17:11.724 --> 17:13.275
You know...

17:13.379 --> 17:17.724
I'm not just collecting blood
for the victims.

17:17.827 --> 17:20.172
We're also collecting
kisses.

17:20.275 --> 17:22.793
Would you like to donate a kiss,
big boy?

17:22.896 --> 17:24.000
Of course.

17:24.103 --> 17:26.241
I'd do anything
for the victims.

17:26.344 --> 17:28.448
Well, then kiss me,
you hunk.

17:28.551 --> 17:33.000
♪♪

17:36.724 --> 17:38.862
Sadly, still no word
on the whereabouts of Daytime

17:38.965 --> 17:41.620
Emmy-Award nominee Andy Richter.

17:41.724 --> 17:44.758
[ Sighing ] Oh! America may soon have
to accept that his life

17:44.862 --> 17:47.172
has been tragically cut short,

17:47.275 --> 17:51.551
much like the multiple network
sitcoms that bore his name.

17:51.655 --> 17:55.482
We have breaking news.

17:55.586 --> 17:58.310
BNN has just received word
that Andy Richter

17:58.413 --> 18:00.517
has survived the tragedy.[ All cheer ]

18:00.620 --> 18:04.206
He's live on the scene,
and we've got the exclusive.

18:04.310 --> 18:08.344
Andy, first off,
on behalf of all of us at BNN,

18:08.448 --> 18:11.034
I would like to welcome you
back from the dead.

18:11.137 --> 18:12.482
It must have been
harrowing.

18:12.586 --> 18:15.586
Yes, and I am grateful
to be alive, Karen.

18:15.689 --> 18:19.310
I had to survive on rainwater
and the tears of the fallen.

18:19.413 --> 18:21.862
Incredible.
You must have been so thirsty.

18:21.965 --> 18:23.517
What else
can you tell us?

18:23.620 --> 18:26.758
In the darkest moments,
I found myself contemplating

18:26.862 --> 18:29.241
mortality, selflessness

18:29.344 --> 18:32.275
and the fact
that love conquers all,

18:32.379 --> 18:34.620
which coincidentally
are all themes

18:34.724 --> 18:36.413
in "The Infinity Conundrum."

18:36.517 --> 18:38.862
That is the movie
you have coming out

18:38.965 --> 18:40.344
in theaters nationwide
next month?

18:40.448 --> 18:43.724
And it's also simultaneously
streaming on demand.

18:43.827 --> 18:46.896
Andy Richter,
alive and well,

18:47.000 --> 18:49.655
controlling the universe
once again.

18:49.758 --> 18:52.862
[ All cheering ]

18:52.965 --> 18:54.758
Christian...

18:54.862 --> 18:57.448
we just got the ratings.

18:57.551 --> 18:58.793
We're number one!

18:58.896 --> 19:03.517
[ All cheer ]

19:03.620 --> 19:05.000
♪♪

19:05.103 --> 19:07.793
I gave blood!

19:07.896 --> 19:09.448
They said I gave
the most blood.

19:09.551 --> 19:11.724
[ All gasp, scream ]

19:11.827 --> 19:13.310
Grace: He donated
too much blood.

19:13.413 --> 19:15.655
We have to get
his blood sugar up.

19:15.758 --> 19:17.448
♪♪

19:17.551 --> 19:24.241
♪ Everybody knows
where the angel lives ♪

19:24.344 --> 19:31.000
♪ Everybody knows
where the angel flies ♪

19:31.103 --> 19:34.103
♪ Everybody sees her face

19:34.206 --> 19:38.068
♪ Brushing up against
their windowpanes ♪

19:38.172 --> 19:39.793
John: Come on, get the fruity.
Get the fruit part in.

19:39.896 --> 19:41.448
What the fuck
are you guys doing?

19:41.551 --> 19:43.758
We're trying to get
his blood sugar back up.

19:43.862 --> 19:45.137
He's choking on the cake!

19:45.241 --> 19:46.413
-[ Gasps ]
-Oh!

19:46.517 --> 19:47.517
-Yeah.
-Damn it!

19:47.620 --> 19:51.137
♪ Everybody knows how
the courageous ♪

19:51.241 --> 19:54.172
Oh

19:54.275 --> 20:01.068
♪ You can feel it in
the birthplace of your heart ♪

20:01.172 --> 20:03.965
♪ Everybody knows inspiration

20:04.068 --> 20:07.655
♪ Even in the wake
of devastation ♪

20:07.758 --> 20:10.724
Bad cake.Paige: Oh, my God.
Grace, you killed him.

20:10.827 --> 20:12.793
Get it out!Come on get it out.
Get it out. Spit it out.

20:12.896 --> 20:14.448
[ Gasps ]

20:14.551 --> 20:16.965
♪ I've been waiting
my whole life ♪

20:17.068 --> 20:21.241
♪ Just to walk with you

20:21.344 --> 20:25.586
♪ And I've been waiting my
whole life to hear your voice ♪

20:25.689 --> 20:29.034
♪ And I know it's gonna
be my choice ♪

20:29.137 --> 20:33.344
♪ It will happen to me,
of course ♪

20:33.448 --> 20:36.379
♪ I will be ready [ Coughs ]

20:36.482 --> 20:40.137
[ All cheer ]

20:40.241 --> 20:46.517
♪ I will be ready

20:46.620 --> 20:55.689
♪♪

20:55.793 --> 20:57.241
[ Ding, ding, ding!]

20:57.344 --> 20:59.620
100!

21:05.448 --> 21:06.448
[ Ding!]

21:10.827 --> 21:11.724
Here is a little slice of hope

21:11.827 --> 21:13.137
on an otherwise dark day.

21:13.241 --> 21:15.862
A group of Hampton DeVille
employees

21:15.965 --> 21:17.689
came together to save a big boy

21:17.793 --> 21:18.689
with a big heart

21:18.793 --> 21:20.275
who passed out after donating

21:20.379 --> 21:22.413
too much blood to the victims.

21:22.517 --> 21:24.482
Oh, my God.
We're heroes.[ Ding! ]
